SUMMARY:TaborSpace Game Night
DESCRIPTION:Portland Area Board Games and RPGs\nThis is the Portland Board Games TaborSpace group.\n\nCome play games at the lovely TaborSpace!\n\nBring your favorite games or play some of ours. We're happy to teach. Ticket to Ride\, Wingspan\, Rummikub\, Carcassonne\, Small World\, and much more. Strategy\, luck\, and chance! Cooperative or competitive.\n\nWe usually meet in the Copeland Commons which is nice stained glass and brick\, with plenty of space and tables of different shapes and sizes.\n\nBringing food and drinks (non-alcoholic) is ok\, as long as we clean up at the end of the night.\n\nTaborSpace is located at 5441 SE Belmont St. Enter the building on Belmont Street. There is limited street parking right out front\, and there is a parking lot across the street on 54th Ave.\nSee more at https://taborspace.org\n\nPlease beware that we have to clean up the space and be out the door by 8:30. please stay and help if you can.
